From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Florian=20H=C3=A4nel?= <florian.haenel@echtzeit.solutions>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 13:36:03 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 03/13] platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: fix uninitialized err in
 profile_setup
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

msi_wmi_platform_profile_setup() tested an uninitialized `int err` right after
devm_platform_profile_register() (which returns its result via data->ppdev, not
err). Drop the bogus check; return PTR_ERR_OR_ZERO(data->ppdev). Standalone fix,
upstreamable independently of the feature-descriptor refactor.

Signed-off-by: Florian Hänel <florian.haenel@echtzeit.solutions>
Assisted-by: Claude:claude-opus-4-8
---
 drivers/platform/x86/msi-wmi-platform.c | 4 ----
 1 file changed, 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/platform/x86/msi-wmi-platform.c b/drivers/platform/x86/msi-wmi-platform.c
index 7695e147fcf3..63b5b29400b3 100644
--- a/drivers/platform/x86/msi-wmi-platform.c
+++ b/drivers/platform/x86/msi-wmi-platform.c
@@ -1471,16 +1471,12 @@ static int msi_wmi_platform_init(struct msi_wmi_platform_data *data)
 
 static int msi_wmi_platform_profile_setup(struct msi_wmi_platform_data *data)
 {
-	int err;
-
 	if (!data->quirks->shift_mode)
 		return 0;
 
 	data->ppdev = devm_platform_profile_register(
 		&data->wdev->dev, "msi-wmi-platform", data,
 		&msi_wmi_platform_profile_ops);
-	if (err)
-		return err;
 
 	return PTR_ERR_OR_ZERO(data->ppdev);
 }
